{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-timeline-js","path":"/drewrwilson/toolsforactivism/week/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"awesomeList":{"repo":"drewrwilson/toolsforactivism","descriptionHTML":"<div>growing list of digital tools for activism things</div>","description":"growing list of digital tools for activism things"},"awesomeListMeta":{"readmeParsedAt":"2021-06-27T23:35:55.453Z"},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open-source host-it-yourself:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Elizabeth-Warren/Spoke\">Spoke</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Elizabeth-Warren/Spoke\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">185</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":185,\"repo\":\"Elizabeth-Warren/Spoke\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Text-distribution tool for organizations to mobilize supporters and members into action. Spoke allows you to upload phone numbers, customize scripts and assign volunteers to communicate with supporters while allowing organizations to manage the process.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-01T14:13:53.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Software as a service:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://petitions.moveon.org/\">MoveOn's Petition Platform</a> - Start your own petition on MoveOn's hosted platform. If your petition gains traction, MoveOn staff may help support you.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-05-15T15:08:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>The Graveyad</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://thunderclap.it\">Thunderclap</a> - use this to coordinate a group sharing the same message on social media at the same time. You write a tweet, make a campaign, and ask people to pledge to support your campaign. When you reach your goal of a certain number of pledgers, your tweet will automatically be posted to each pledger's social media.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-05-15T15:08:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Software as a service:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://democracy.io\">Democracy.io</a> (<a href=\"https://github.com/sinak/democracy.io\">code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sinak/democracy.io\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">246</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":246,\"repo\":\"sinak/democracy.io\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->) - Send messages to members of the US Senate and House of Representatives.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-02T00:12:09.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Projects to keep an eye on (ie projects in development)</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/securityfirst/Umbrella_android\">Umbrella App</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/securityfirst/Umbrella_android\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">174</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":174,\"repo\":\"securityfirst/Umbrella_android\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - an open source Android App with lessons and checklists on digital and physical security topics ranging from sending a secure mail to dealing with physical surveillance and attending a protest safely. Also includes forms for responding to security incidents and feeds to ensure users are up to date with the latest security information for their area. Also available in Spanish and Chinese.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-01-03T19:26:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Browsers:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/TheTorProject/gettorbrowser\">Tor Browser</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/TheTorProject/gettorbrowser\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">279</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":279,\"repo\":\"TheTorProject/gettorbrowser\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Free software for enabling anonymous communication. It prevents somebody watching your Internet connection from learning what sites you visit, it prevents the sites you visit from learning your physical location, and it lets you access sites which are blocked.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-10-11T09:53:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open-source host-it-yourself:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/EFForg/contact-congress\">Contact Congress (Open Source)</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/EFForg/contact-congress\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">29</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":29,\"repo\":\"EFForg/contact-congress\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Send emails to members of the US Congress. This was developed by EFF as an open source project. They use it for their own campaigns internally. There is also a hosted version run by Fight for the Future (see below).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-06-28T19:30:24.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open-source host-it-yourself:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/fightforthefuture/call-congress\">Call Congress</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/fightforthefuture/call-congress\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">27</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":27,\"repo\":\"fightforthefuture/call-congress\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Coordinate call-in days to US Congress, the President, or local or corporate targets. Original project from Fight for the Future and Taskforce.is, but with lots of development from <a href=\"https://github.com/mozilla/call-congress\">Mozilla</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mozilla/call-congress\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1,\"repo\":\"mozilla/call-congress\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> and the <a href=\"https://github.com/effOrg/call-congress/tree/refactor/master\">EFF</a>. Frontend looks like this, <a href=\"https://call.mozilla.org/\">https://call.mozilla.org</a> and the backend looks like <a href=\"http://callpower.org/easy-to-use/\">http://callpower.org</a>. A hosted version is available, and the code is AGPL.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-06-28T19:30:24.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open-source host-it-yourself:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://civicrm.org/\">CiviCRM</a> - Contact management system for non-profit / activist sector, including donations, memberships, events, SMS, bulk mail &#x26; full CRM.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-04-09T21:15:39.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Software as a service:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://actionnetwork.org\">Action Network</a> - A nonprofit digital organizing toolset for progressive organizations. Includes petitions, advocacy, fundraising, mass email, and more for free or cheap.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-11-16T03:23:28.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Projects to keep an eye on (ie projects in development)</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/code-corps\">Code Corps</a> - code corps hopes to provide tools that connect people to projects that have a social impact, facilitate crowdfunding, and provide support for those working on projects</li>","updatedAt":"2016-08-19T20:13:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Operating Systems:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://tails.boum.org/\">Tails</a> - A live media, Linux-based operating system that is designed to allow the use of a computer without leaving a digital footprint.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-05T07:00:22.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open-source host-it-yourself:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.ushahidi.com/\">Ushahidi</a> - Platform for data management and visualization. Other tools include CrowdMap, CrisisNET (data about world crises), Ping (tool for checking is someone is ok after an emergency), SMSsync (two-way SMS gateway). Check out their <a href=\"https://github.com/ushahidi\">github repos</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-01-20T21:24:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Projects to keep an eye on (ie projects in development)</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/the-learning-collective/whereat-macroid\">Where@</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/the-learning-collective/whereat-macroid\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">37</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":37,\"repo\":\"the-learning-collective/whereat-macroid\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - a mobile app to help protesters communicate with each other in realtime during marches</li>","updatedAt":"2016-01-20T21:24:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Software as a service:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://riseup.net/\">Riseup</a> - A provider of communication tools for activists, including free webmail, chat, and VPN</li>","updatedAt":"2016-01-07T21:35:54.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open-source host-it-yourself:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/drewrwilson/countdown\">Countdown</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/drewrwilson/countdown\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">35</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":35,\"repo\":\"drewrwilson/countdown\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A quick &#x26; simple tool for making your own webpage with a countdown to your upcoming event.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-12-31T05:13:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Software as a service:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.loomio.org/\">Loomio</a> - Tool for collaborative decision-making in groups. Note: Loomio's <a href=\"https://github.com/loomio/loomio\">code is also open source</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/loomio/loomio\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.1k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2053,\"repo\":\"loomio/loomio\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->, but it's generally used as a hosted service.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-12-31T04:56:44.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Software as a service:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.controlshiftlabs.com/\">ControlShift</a> - Distributed petitions, events and local groups for progressive advocacy organizations. Tools to help make campaigns more participatory.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-12-31T04:56:44.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Projects to keep an eye on (ie projects in development)</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/handsupwalkout/handsupwalkout.github.io\">Day of Action</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/handsupwalkout/handsupwalkout.github.io\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">8</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":8,\"repo\":\"handsupwalkout/handsupwalkout.github.io\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - very rough tool used to coordinate a day of action for high school students. the starting point for a more generalized tool to run a day of action campaign</li>","updatedAt":"2015-12-31T04:56:44.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Software as a service:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.change.org/\">Change.org</a> Petition site. Chose a target, make a petition, send it to your friends. If they get traction, Change.org has staff that can provide support. (They also have org accounts, that allow groups to do branded pages and export contact info of signers.)</li>","updatedAt":"2015-11-17T14:40:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open-source host-it-yourself:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.victorykitapp.com\">VictoryKit</a> - Optimize petition campaign content. Not actively maintained.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-27T22:47:01.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open-source host-it-yourself:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/controlshift/prague-server\">TakeCharge.io</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/controlshift/prague-server\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">9</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":9,\"repo\":\"controlshift/prague-server\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - opensource or SaaS online donations powered by Stripe.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-27T22:43:55.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Projects to keep an eye on (ie projects in development)</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://drewrwilson.com/stencilvalidator/\">Stencil Validator</a> (<a href=\"https://github.com/drewrwilson/stencilvalidator\">code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/drewrwilson/stencilvalidator\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">12</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":12,\"repo\":\"drewrwilson/stencilvalidator\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->) - a design tool for determining if your artwork is a valid stencil</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T19:36:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open-source host-it-yourself:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/lockitron/selfstarter\">Self Starter</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/lockitron/selfstarter\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":3151,\"repo\":\"lockitron/selfstarter\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - roll your own crowdfunding site</li>","updatedAt":"2015-08-12T21:24:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open-source host-it-yourself:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/therules/CrowdRing\">Crowdring</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/therules/CrowdRing\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">15</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":15,\"repo\":\"therules/CrowdRing\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - web app where people around the world can place a free missed call to sign a petition</li>","updatedAt":"2015-08-12T21:03:19.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Open-source host-it-yourself:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Twilio-org/rapid-response-kit\">Twilio.org's Rapid Response Kit</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Twilio-org/rapid-response-kit\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">298</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":298,\"repo\":\"Twilio-org/rapid-response-kit\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Collection phone-related tools using Twilio's service. Kit includes: Auto-Respond (inbound voice/sms responder), Broadcast (simple way to broadcast texts/calls to a list), Conference Line, Forwarder, Ringdown (call down a list of people, if 1st person doesn't answer go on to the next), Help Line (Press 1 for..., Press 2 for...)</li>","updatedAt":"2015-08-12T14:33:42.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Software as a service:</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://congress.fightforthefuture.org/\">Contact Congress (FFTF)</a> - Used to send emails to members of the US Congress. This is Fight for the Future's hosted-version of the open sources Contact Congress. Ideal for organizations that send a lot of emails to congress, but who don't have tech staff who can install and maintain their own version of the open source software.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-08-12T14:33:42.000Z"}]},"previous":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/gamontal/awesome-katas","repo":"gamontal/awesome-katas"},"next":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/dylanrees/citizen-science","repo":"dylanrees/citizen-science"}},"pageContext":{"type":"week","repo":"drewrwilson/toolsforactivism","id":"awesomes/github.com/drewrwilson/toolsforactivism","previousId":"awesomes/github.com/gamontal/awesome-katas","nextId":"awesomes/github.com/dylanrees/citizen-science"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","3289010534"]}